t\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nRight. Looking at the table:\\n\\n- **Claude Code**: Could add `PostToolUse[Bash]` → Alive\\n- **Gemini CLI**: Already has `after-tool *` → Alive (free)\\n- **OpenCode**: No per-tool hooks → stuck with 24h threshold\\n- **Cursor**: No per-tool hooks → stuck with 24h threshold\\n- **Factory AI**: Same hook system as Claude Code, could add `PostToolUse[Bash]` → Alive\\n\\nSo we'd end up with two code paths regardless — agents with Alive support get tight detection, agents without fall back to the 24h threshold. That's more complexity for a marginal improvement over just using 24h everywhere.\\n\\nAnd honestly, the 24h threshold already covers the real-world cases well. No agent turn lasts a full day. The zombie scenario it protects against (killed agent condensing into every commit) requires the session to be >24h stale, which means at least one full day of commits before the overlap check kicks in. In practice that's fine — a single extra condensation of stale data isn't harmful.\\n\\nI think the Alive hook is a good idea for the future (it'd be useful for more than just this), but it's not necessary to solve this bug. Want to go with the 24h threshold as-is and move on?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1834,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":156327,\"output_tokens\":308,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1834,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYeRLtxSJokrowRHZpQEZ\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"84f3b737-650a-4e3b-9518-1922aad00352\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T14:35:35.548Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"84f3b737-650a-4e3b-9518-1922aad00352\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"se